### API Testing for Finance Dashboard

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000
# Replace your token here manually by following the steps below
@authToken = your_token_here

### 1. Login as Default Admin
# Expected: Returns a token and user details. Copy the token and paste it in @authToken above.
POST {{baseUrl}}/users/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin@finance.com",
  "password": "admin123"
}

### ----------------------------------------------------
### 2. User & Role Management (Admin Only)
### ----------------------------------------------------

### Create a new user (Analyst)
POST {{baseUrl}}/users
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "analyst2@finance.com",
  "password": "password123",
  "role": "ANALYST"
}

### Get all users
GET {{baseUrl}}/users
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### Update User Role & Status (Admin Only)
# Note: Replace <USER_ID> with an ID from the GET /users response
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/users/<USER_ID>
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "role": "VIEWER",
  "status": "INACTIVE"
}

### Delete a User (Admin Only)
# Note: Replace <USER_ID> with an ID from the GET /users response
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/users/<USER_ID>
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### ----------------------------------------------------
### 3. Financial Records Management
### ----------------------------------------------------

### Create a new Income Record (Admin)
POST {{baseUrl}}/records
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "amount": 5000,
  "type": "INCOME",
  "category": "Salary",
  "date": "2026-04-01T10:00:00Z",
  "notes": "April Salary"
}

### Create a new Expense Record (Admin)
POST {{baseUrl}}/records
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "amount": 200,
  "type": "EXPENSE",
  "category": "Software",
  "date": "2026-04-02T10:00:00Z",
  "notes": "Github Copilot Subscription"
}

### List All Records (Admin / Analyst)
GET {{baseUrl}}/records
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### List Records with Advanced Filtering (Date & Category)
GET {{baseUrl}}/records?type=INCOME&category=Salary&startDate=2026-04-01T00:00:00Z&endDate=2026-04-30T00:00:00Z
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### Update a Record (Admin Only)
# Note: Replace <RECORD_ID> with an ID from the GET /records response
PUT {{baseUrl}}/records/<RECORD_ID>
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "amount": 5500,
  "type": "INCOME",
  "category": "Salary",
  "date": "2026-04-01T10:00:00Z",
  "notes": "Updated April Salary with Bonus"
}

### Delete a Record (Admin Only)
# Note: Replace <RECORD_ID> with an ID from the GET /records response
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/records/<RECORD_ID>
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### ----------------------------------------------------
### 4. Dashboard Summaries
### ----------------------------------------------------

### Get Dashboard Statistics (Income, Expense, Net Balance, Recent Activity)
GET {{baseUrl}}/dashboard/summary
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### Get Category-wise Breakdown
GET {{baseUrl}}/dashboard/category-totals
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### Get Monthly Trends
GET {{baseUrl}}/dashboard/monthly-trends
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### ----------------------------------------------------
### 5. Validation & Error Handling Tests
### ----------------------------------------------------

### Test 1: Invalid Amount (Should return 400 Bad Request from Zod validation)
POST {{baseUrl}}/records
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "amount": -500, 
  "type": "INCOME",
  "category": "Salary",
  "date": "2026-04-01T10:00:00Z"
}

### Test 2: Missing Fields & Duplicate User (Should return 400)
POST {{baseUrl}}/users
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin@finance.com" 
}

### Test 3: Wrong/No Token (Should return 401 Unauthorized)
GET {{baseUrl}}/records
Authorization: Bearer invalid_token_here

### ----------------------------------------------------
### 6. Access Control Check (Validation)
### ----------------------------------------------------
# If you extract a token by creating a Viewer credential from the login endpoint, 
# and then try to create a record, it should throw a 403 Forbidden error.
